Third-party material
================================================================================

Vendored Hyprland metadata (`meta/`)
------------------------------------
`meta/hl.meta.lua` and the derived `meta/hyprland-config-keys.txt` are vendored,
unmodified, from the Hyprland project (https://github.com/hyprwm/Hyprland),
which is distributed under the BSD-3-Clause license:

    Copyright (c) 2022-2026, vaxerski and Hyprland contributors

These files are used only as build-time/test-time reference data (the
authoritative set of configuration option keys) and are not compiled into the
distributed binary. hyprconf is an independent project and is not affiliated
with or endorsed by the Hyprland project; the choice of license for hyprconf is
independent of Hyprland's.

Fonts / glyphs
--------------
hyprconf ships no fonts. Section/collection icons are ordinary Unicode/emoji
code points rendered with whatever system fonts are installed; no glyph assets
are bundled or redistributed.

Rust dependencies
-----------------
hyprconf builds on the Rust crate ecosystem (iced, full_moon, indexmap,
directories, serde, toml, glob, thiserror, anyhow, tracing, and their
transitive dependencies). Each is distributed under its own license (typically
MIT, Apache-2.0, or both); run `cargo tree` / `cargo about` to enumerate them.
